---
description: Agent modules under agents/ must follow agents/<agent_name>/{index.php,config/,src/,tests/} structure and shared include patterns
globs: agents/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

- **Each agent MUST be self-contained under `V:\\agents\\<agent_name>\\`**
  - Standard layout is documented and reflected across the codebase:
    - Entry: `index.php` (or other UI entry like `viewer.php`)
    - Configuration: `config/` (`config.php` + `config.json`)
    - Source: `src/` (classes and repositories)
    - Tests: `tests/` (when present)
  - Reference: [V:\agents\AGENTS.md](mdc:agents/AGENTS.md) lines 11-23.

- **Agent code MUST use root shared includes via `__DIR__`**
  - Agents are typically 2 levels deep, so shared includes must be referenced with `../../includes/...`.
  - Reference: [V:\agents\AGENTS.md](mdc:agents/AGENTS.md) lines 79-85 and 238-239.

```php
require_once __DIR__ . '/../../includes/connect.php';
```

- **Agent `src/` files SHOULD use PascalCase class filenames and class names**
  - Common pattern in `agents/*/src/`:
    - `*Repository.php` for DB access
    - `*Validator.php` for validation rules
    - `*Agent.php` for orchestration
  - Example: [V:\agents\ability_agent\src\AbilityRepository.php](mdc:agents/ability_agent/src/AbilityRepository.php)

- **Agent DB access MUST use the shared `db_*` helpers**
  - See [V:\includes\connect.php](mdc:includes/connect.php) for `db_fetch_one`, `db_fetch_all`, `db_execute`, `db_transaction`.
